				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Why do Shamans continue to insist on using Fire pets for Rak`Ashiir? It's starting to drive me nuts.
<br />

<br />
In all my experiences fighting Rak`Ashiir since the resist changes, not once has a fire pet resisted the AE. In fact the AE is usually enough to kill the fire pet outright.
<br />

<br />
I maintain that using a High HP and High DPS pet (57 earth, 61 air, 65 earth, or epic) is by far the best way to fighting him. Fire resist buffs on the mage are definitely must if you hope to resist it.
<br />

<br />
A mage with Planar Renewal or Transon's Elemental Renewal, a cleric with Complete Heal, or a shaman with Kragg's Mending is the only healing needed.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://members.cox.net/jmattcrews/xalsig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
